cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.AL, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with the minimum dominating set problem in the CONGEST model, which is a well-studied problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The CONGEST model is a network-based model, which is related to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper deals with connected dominating set, which is a subproblem of dominating set, and hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category.
